questions.explanation:
&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The logic followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Logic: &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;(1st number &amp;times; 3rd number) &amp;divide; 2 = 2nd number&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Now,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;For, (17, 68, 8)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; (17 &amp;times; 8) &amp;divide; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;= 136 &amp;divide; 2 = 68.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;For, (16, 72, 9)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rarr; (16 &amp;times; 9) &amp;divide; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;= 144 &amp;divide; 2 = 72.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Similarly, for &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;(10, 105, 21)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rarr; (10 &amp;times; 21) &amp;divide; 2 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;= 210 &amp;divide; 2 = 105.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Option 2&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let, the two numbers be &amp;lsquo;a&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;b&amp;rsquo; (such that a &amp;gt; b)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sum of two numbers is 14: (a + b) = 14 &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;---(i)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And, the difference of their squares is 112: a&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - b&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 112&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The formula of a&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - b&lt;sup&gt;2 &lt;/sup&gt;is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - b&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = (a + b) (a - b)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Substituting the values in the formula, we get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;112 = 14 (a - b)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(a - b) = 8 &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;---(ii)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On adding (i) and (ii), we get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a + b + a - b = 14 + 8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2a = 22&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a = 11&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, substituting the value of a in (i) we get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;11 + b = 14&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;b = 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, the numbers are 11 and 3.&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &amp;rsquo;11 and 3&amp;rsquo; is the correct answer.

&lt;p&gt;The logic followed here is:\&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In one minute, minute hand moves = 360/ 60 = 6&amp;ordm;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In one hour, hour&amp;nbsp;hand moves = 360/ 12&amp;nbsp;= 30&amp;ordm;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In one minute hour hand moves = 30/60 = 1/2&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;ordm;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;So, the relative distance between both the hands in one minute =&amp;nbsp;6&amp;ordm; -&amp;nbsp;1/2&amp;ordm; =&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(5 {1 \over 2}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;ordm;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In other words, in one minute, the minute hand gains&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(5 {1 \over 2}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;ordm;&amp;nbsp; more than hour hand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In one hour the gain will be&amp;nbsp; =&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(5 {1 \over 2}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;ordm;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;times;&amp;nbsp;60 = 330&amp;ordm;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In other words, the minute hand will gain [ 330/6 = 55] 55 minutes to the hour hand. or the minute hand moves by 55 minutes in an hour.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &amp;#39;55&amp;#39; is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

